item.title: Love Your Enemies
item.description:
Love Your Enemies
Hey bubbiful ones! Live like bright lamps! ^_^ Don't drink the "ass milk" lol... erm yeah... It's been a while since I made one of these!! ^_^ I missed talking to you guys. So here is some Bubz quality time (pukes). So are you guys willing to share this resolution with me? You should! Because you are Worth it! Everybody will hate or resent at many points of their lives. But what I'm saying- with a lil bit of understanding; we can resent less. We can appreciate situations more. I'm using my macbook isight webcam for this video because I'm staying with my granny and I didn't bring my camcorder. Hope you don't mind guys!! Still mid-sick with the flu but getting better-ish ^_^. If it doesn't kill me, only gets me stronger yo!! Being negative/hateful will only hurt yourself in the process. Is it really worth it? Will it benefit you? Answer: No. It will only make you trapped in resentment. Whether 2010 was good for you or not, we now have 2011 in front of us. Leave all of the bad baggage behind. If you haven't already; its time to live for the future and not the past. Very often in life we are driven by many different factors that delays/prevents us from being happy. One common factor that can drive us is 'Resentment'. Honestly; I don't know everything but I'm just going to talk about some pointers that will hopefully inspire you to live less negative. I hope this video can become viral and work viral to break away grudges in people's hearts. Grudges are unhealthy. You know what? I really don't like the whole 'makeup guru' status. I'm not a guru. My channel is a 'Guru' channel just so my videos can be found easier. I hope you guys will listen to me like a friend or a sister and realise not everything I say may be 'right' but will be from my heart. I recently hit 500,000 subscribers on Youtube. What a great start to the New Year. I am just so happy for each and every one of you guys. Thank you so much for these awesome 2 years. I feel like you guys walked alongside with us as I grew up. You probably don't see it yourself but you guys are amazing. Thank you for being my lamps ^_^ Big thanks to my big sis Claire for inspiring me to make this video. She and I had this kick ass talk that i will never forget. ^^ Follow me on Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/bubzbeauty Bubzbeauty Official Website: http://www.bubzbeauty.com Shop the Bubbi Clothing Line: http://bubbi.bubzbeauty.com Connect with me at the Bubzbeauty Fanpage where I chill n catch up with you guys ^^ http://www.facebook.com/pages/Bubzbeauty-Official/181811348879

item.title: Inbetweeners - Rude Road Trip - Red Nose Day
item.description:
Inbetweeners - Rude Road Trip - Red Nose Day
Comic Relief - The Inbetweeners rev it up on Rude Road Trip. Facebook link - http://www.facebook.com/e4inbetweeners?v=app_176203492417725#!/e4inbetweeners?v=app_176203492417725 Just as the nation prepares to do something funny for money in celebration of Red Nose Day 2011, the four stars of the hit comedy show The Inbetweeners are already paving the way by embarking on a naughty road trip to visit the rudest and crudest place names in the country. The cheeky chaps, actors Simon Bird, Joe Thomas, James Buckley and Blake Harrison (otherwise known as Will, Simon, Jay and Neil) have challenged themselves to visit 50 lewd locations in just 50 hours and are expected to stop off at places such as Minge Lane, Titty Ho and Bell End. And no, we're not making these up. Despite laughs a plenty along the way, the boys are on a serious mission to raise cash and help change lives - and they're calling for the nation to show their support by making a donation to Comic Relief. The funny foursome will travel along their risqué route in the classic yellow Fiat, a regular feature in the smash hit series, and the cameras will be rolling the entire time to catch all the banter as they navigate their way around the county in their rude race against the clock. To help them reach their target in such a short space of time, the public are invited to suggest where the lads should visit through their Facebook page and they'll take snaps at every location as proof of their loitering at the funniest named places in Britain. So come on Fwends! Back the boys and make a donation to help them raise a packet. Your contribution will undoubtedly help to transform the lives of poor, vulnerable and disadvantaged people both here in the UK and across Africa.
